context: The members of the city council are each elected from <a4_0><b9_0>single member districts within the city<b9_0/><a4_0/>. The mayor and city attorney are elected directly by the <a0_0><b5_0>voters of the entire city<b5_0/><a0_0/>. The mayor, city attorney, and council members are elected to <a1_0><b6_0>four-year terms<b6_0/>,<a1_0/> with a two-term limit. Elections are held on a non-partisan basis per California state law; nevertheless, most officeholders do identify themselves as either Democrats or Republicans. In 2007, registered <a2_0><b7_0>Democrats outnumbered Republicans by about 7 to 6<b7_0/><a2_0/> in the city, and Democrats currently (as of 2015[update]) hold a 5-4 majority in the city council.
